rComments: Great prof! Friendly and approchable, extremely fair marker, and besides her sometimes monotone voice, she's very engaging (which I think just further shows how interesting she is!).
Lovely professor, and perfect for the course. She is engaging and interesting, even though she sometimes wanders from the topic a bit. Always wonderful class discussions.
Awesome Professor!  The only reason why i took the course was because it fit into my schedule...I went in expecting to hate it, but it ended up being the most enjoyable course of the year!

Professor Jackson is extremely articulate. She is always able to find the most precise and appropriate words for what she wants to express. She cares about her students; she's friendly in/out of class and replies to emails and gives feedback quickly. She does sometimes rush because there are so many readings for the class. Still, recommended.

Wonderful teacher! Engaging lecturer. There's a lot of material to cover but it's organized very well and is all actually interesting. It leads into the others, allows connections to be made. Recommended.
She is really nice, approachable and makes poetry fun and interesting. By talking about the histories behind the poems, it almost makes the works come alive!
Decisive. Perspicacious. And wastes no words. She's also really nice and approachable. We need more profs like her at UToronto.
Love how she says the f-word with that English accent...too much reading, but at least she's nice.
Amazing Prof; Very Nice, Very Smart
